    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="518" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                <head>No. 514.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">de
                                    Zamacona</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Mexico</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-08-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 18,
                                1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary</hi>: With much gratification this
                            legation has learned of the instructions which have been given to the
                            governor of Arizona to investigate the abuses complained of to your
                            Department in my note of the 25th of July last, to the end of procuring
                            the punishment of the guilty parties, and for maintaining, if possible,
                            order and peace in that part of the frontier. The note which under
                            to-day’s date I address to your Department concerning the recent crimes
                            committed by organized <pb facs="0968" n="844" xml:id="pg_844"/> parties
                            of evil-doers from this side of the boundary line, and of which several
                            Mexican residents of the State of Sonora have been the victims, will
                            amply show your Department how well founded are the instructions given
                            to the governor of Arizona, and how gratifying it will be if they can be
                            carried into effect.</p>
                <p>I repeat to you, Mr. Secretary, upon this occasion, the assurances of my
                            deepest consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M. DE ZAMACONA.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
